observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed that:

1.	The Municipal HRMO ensure the prompt submission of Daily Time Records (DTRs) and other necessary documents to the Municipal Accountant to serve as bases for the computation of payroll;

2.	The Municipal Accountant ensure the completeness of all documentary requirements for the cash advance and liquidation of payroll

In view of the above observations, we recommended that the Management adhere to the provisions stated in the Department of Finance (DOF)-Bureau of Local Government Finance (BLGF) Local Treasury Operations Manual and the Local Government Code of 1991 as follows:

Provide the accountable officers with fireproof vaults or safe safekeeping and the storage of cash and other valuable documents to deter theft and to protect assets against loss;

Require the Collecting Officers and Market Collectors and other authorized personnel  receiving collections outside of the local government office, the use of Teller’s/Collector’s  Cashbook to record all collections received and all remittances to the designated Liquidating Officer; 

Renew the fidelity bond of the bondable officers of the Municipality on time; and

Prohibit the Collecting Officers from utilizing the cash on hand for the purpose of encashing private checks.
